Airbnb’s **2024 adjustment for Stock-based Compensation Expense was $1.418 billion** (i.e., **$1,418 million**), added back in the shareholder letter’s reconciliation of net income to Adjusted EBITDA.

For context, Airbnb’s subsequently filed 2024 Form 10-K presents **$1.407 billion** as stock-based compensation and classifies another **$11 million**—amortization of previously capitalized stock-based compensation—within depreciation and amortization. Thus, the shareholder-letter adjustment is:

**$1.407 billion + $0.011 billion = $1.418 billion.**

